+ runs on each node, meaning also on the control plane
+ updating networking rules on nodes
+ TCP, UDP, SCTP streams stream forwarding or  
  random forwarding across a set of pod backends of an application
+ implements forwarding rules defined by user through service api objects
+ interacts with firewall on the node (e.g. iptables)
  + configures iptables rules to capture the traffic for its ClusterIP
    and forwards it to one of the Service's endpoints
+ watches api server on the control plane for crud operations on services and endpoints

